Hill-Rom Careers – Jobs at Hill-Rom | Join a medical device leader




































About Hill-Rom
We are a medical technology company relentlessly focused on improving the lives of patients and caregivers around the world. With $2.7B in global revenue and over 10,000 employees, we serve healthcare professionals in over 100 countries. We occupy an exciting space in healthcare, and we want you to be a part of it.
 








Our Mission
Every day, around the world, we enhance outcomes for patients and their caregivers.









Find Your Career Path


Research & DevelopmentWe are a medical technology company, and innovation is at the core of our DNA. Be a part of a team that’s changing the way patients experience care.Learn More 
Field ServiceLike working with your hands as well as your mind? Find a challenging career working on-site with our valued customers.Learn More 
SalesBy connecting patients and caregivers to some of the most advanced innovations Hill-Rom has to offer, our sales professionals are shaping the way healthcare is delivered.Learn More 


Global Supply ChainWe’re obsessed with improving how we source, manufacture and deliver our quality products around the world.Learn More 
FinanceMake your mark on Hill-Rom’s bottom line by putting your financial expertise to work with us.Learn More 
ITWe’re re-inventing enterprise architecture, utilizing the cloud, focusing on mobile applications and giving ambitious technologists the opportunity to build something great.Learn More 











Hill-Rom Careers






Working for a healthier world.
Make a difference in the lives of others — and your own.

Search Jobs






Corporate Social Responsibility


Philanthropy Meets Environmental Concern
We view good corporate citizenship as a natural extension of our mission. We sponsor numerous employee volunteer opportunities, including our Hospital Beds for Humanity® program, charitable gifts programs and partnerships with leading non-profits such as the United Way and Red Cross. To reduce waste, many of our products are refurbished and returned to the market, or the materials are recycled to reclaim metals, plastics and electronic components. At Hill-Rom you’ll always find an outlet for your passion to improve the lives, and community, around you.







Our History


A History of Innovation
We draw on a heritage of more than 85 years of innovation and excellence to provide solutions that enhance outcomes for patients and their caregivers.
Rooted in our founder William A. Hillenbrand’s dream to “bring the home into the hospital,” we have grown into an industry leader and a trusted partner to healthcare providers, caregivers and patients around the world.
Every day we build on our legacy of making a difference in the lives of those we touch.












Our Products & Innovation


We are a leading innovator of medical technology focusing on patient care solutions that improve clinical outcomes in five core areas: Advancing Mobility, Wound Care and Prevention, Patient Monitoring and Diagnostics, Surgical Safety and Efficiency, and Respiratory Health. Our products are grouped within three portfolio types.
 
Patient Support Systems
Caregivers in hospital settings rely on our Patient Support Systems offerings every day. This portfolio includes bed frames, support surfaces and mattresses, Liko® Lifts, stretchers, Clinical Workflow Solutions (CWS) and other medical technologies.
 
 
 
Front Line Care
Front Line Care includes a portfolio of Welch Allyn® products such as patient monitoring and diagnostic equipment, and other practical innovations typically delivered at the point of care in doctors’ offices and examination rooms. We also offer world-class Respiratory Care products such as Monarch™ Airway Clearance System, The Vest® System, VitalCough® System and MetaNeb® System. Mortara Instrument boasts a complete line of diagnostic cardiology and patient monitoring solutions to serve clinicians.
 
Surgical Solutions
Hill-Rom’s world-class surgical solutions are found in operating rooms worldwide. Allen Medical produces advanced surgical positioning equipment that enhances surgical access. Aspen Surgical is a leading manufacturer of medical supplies and surgical products including Bard-Parker® Blades and Scalpels. Trumpf Medical provides an advanced range of OR products, including modular OR tables and revolutionary LED surgical lights.




Our Growth


Building Sustainable & Profitable Businesses
By nearly every measure, fiscal 2016 was a record setting-year for our company. Hill-Rom achieved record sales and profitability while strengthening our foundation for future growth.
Hill‑Rom’s focus on differentiated and connected solutions that improve patient care is an integral part of our strategy. Our R&D, Engineering, Manufacturing and Marketing colleagues are collaborating to develop new products and services across our Patient Support Systems, Surgical Solutions and Front Line Care businesses that will further expand and enhance our customer partnerships, and help them solve the challenges they face.















Our Diversity


Building Inclusive Teams for a Stronger Business
At Hill-Rom, we embrace and value a diverse and inclusive culture. We believe our decision making will be better, our culture will be stronger and our performance as a company will improve when we give everyone a seat at the table. We are a global company located in over 100 countries around the world, and we strive to achieve a workforce that reflects the diverse group of patients and caregivers that we serve every day. Hill-Rom is an equal employment employer F/M/Disability/Vet/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity.







Corporate Offices



Hill-Rom Chicago, IL -  Map
Our downtown Chicago office is conveniently located in Prudential Plaza, just off Michigan Avenue near Millennium Park.  We’re conveniently located next to many Chicago Transit Authority (CTA) and Metra stops.
 
 
Hill-Rom Batesville, IN -  Map
Located in beautiful southeastern Indiana, our Batesville office is our largest facility employing nearly 2,000 people. The campus houses Hill-Rom’s operational center where the bulk of our administrative and manufacturing functions reside. Batesville is located off I-74, about one hour southeast of Indianapolis and one hour northwest of Cincinnati.
 
Hill-Rom Amsterdam -  Map
Our European headquarters is located just south of downtown Amsterdam in the Bijlmermeer area. The Bullewijk metro station is conveniently located nearby and is served by 2 lines (the 50 and 54).



